Packages:
Compression and archives packages- tar and zip

Compress a file:
$ gzip filename
Decompress  package:
$ gunzip filename.gz

For multiple files use tar:
Create an archive:

$ tar czf archivename.tar file1 file2 file3
c- create
z- display the process of archiving
f- preceding the filename of the archive

Unpack and archive:
$ tar xvf archivename.tar
x- extract

How to install packages?
The most common package managements are apt, yum, rpg , dpkg

Install a package using apt and yum
$ apt install packagename
$ yum install packagename

Remove a package
$ apt remove packagename
$ apt remove packagename
